^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, my comments. With 4-4 in the majors, the responder to 1N should always bid Stayman, because it is usually better to play in a 4-4 fit if possible. And, over a weak NT, I like to play "major suit garbage Stayman." That means, even if partner bids 2@D over 2@C, the responder can then bid 2@H, showing 4-4 or better in the major. The NT opener passes if his hearts are better, and corrects to 2@S if his spades are better. In this case ira's hearts were better, so he passed, but if his hearts and spades were reversed, he could bid 2@S.|
