^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|ally's 8 of hearts back at trick three was a suit preference for diamonds. Good play. The other play I want to discuss was Dee's "loser on loser" play at trick eleven. it was quite good. The idea here is that I was ruffing with a natural trump trick anyway  and dee has diamond losers. so she might as well pitch her diamond loser, since it doesn't cost anything. If she had overruffed with the Ace, she would lose an additional trick, the 8 of spades plus the 2 diamonds. |
